        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20588\">#20588</a> is a first small step in this direction. It introduces the predicate <code>AbsoluteValue.IsNontrivial</code>, which simplifies handling the distinction between trivial and nontrivial absolute values (without the need for a decidability instance).</p>",
