    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"479359\">Michael Stoll</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Absolute.20values.20are.20equivalent.20iff.2E.2E.2E/near/493006698\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20642\">#20642</a> extends the API for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs#doc\">docs#WithAbs</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs.equiv#doc\">docs#WithAbs.equiv</a> .</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It occurred to me that most of the API lemmas for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs.equiv#doc\">docs#WithAbs.equiv</a> can be gotten rid of by replacing <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs.equiv#doc\">docs#WithAbs.equiv</a> with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs.ringEquiv#doc\">docs#WithAbs.ringEquiv</a> (i.e., use the ring isomorphism instead of just a bijection). I do that in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20713\">#20713</a>; there was only one place downstream where <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs.ringEquiv#doc\">docs#WithAbs.ringEquiv</a> was used (which the PR deprecates in favor of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=WithAbs.equiv#doc\">docs#WithAbs.equiv</a> with the now same definition); the API lemmas are so far used nowhere in Mathlib.</p>",
